This paper deals with machine learning and text information extraction for detecting and ranking cyber threat events in Twitter. The paper focuses on detecting both novel and developing events using an unsupervised machine learning approach, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the extraction of named entities and keywords, which could place it in the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SD).
